{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7713710e-51c8-4c9b-9f07-f7a8cb998ef4","content":"In .NET MAUI, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>()\n        .ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n        {\n#if ANDROID\n            events.AddAndroid(android => android\n                .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n                .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n#if IOS\n            events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n                .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n        });\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` compiler directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- Android gives you the `Activity`; iOS gives you the `UIApplication`.\n- Other events are available too (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1abb4ec2-ee81-4203-8477-9a45a1f6b024","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI, specifically:\n- Android: OnPause/OnStop\n- iOS: DidEnterBackground\n\nThis is a knowledge question about .NET MAUI development. I can answer this directly from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase, since this is a general programming question rather than a repo-specific one.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, you can hook into platform-specific lifecycle events using the `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` method in your `MauiProgram.cs`. This uses the `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n\n\nNow I'll show them how to implement this with a code example that demonstrates configuring the lifecycle events for both Android and iOS platforms.","outputTokens":452,"requestId":"4849:362770:70DAEB6:7D35DD7:69F3FAD6"},"id":"6d224430-a723-4f79-97fe-f943c20c2d6a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00: